            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-12-30T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-12-30T19:00:00-05:00" n="856" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d856">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Strong, Robert C.: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Taipei</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Edgar</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-12-30T19:00:00-05:00">December 30, 1949—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>598. Robert C. Strong transferred Taipei Charge d’Affaires (First Secretary)
                    EmbOff Taipei and Consul [at] ConGen Taipei effective day following receipt this
                    telegram. Submit 353 showing effective date. TO 0–13341 Dec 30 OA–238220
                    authorizes transportation effects Hong Kong to Taipei. If no effects to be
                    shipped under this order please notify Department by telegram so that TO can be
                    canceled.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
